We can think of $\color{blue}\color{black}5\color{black} \div \color{green}1\color{black}$ as putting $\color{blue}D5$ circles into  $\color{green}1$ group:[[image 0]]
How many circles are in the group?
$\color{blue}\color{black}5\color{black} \div \color{green}1 = {5}$
We can think of $\color{blue}\color{black}2\color{black} \div \color{green}1\color{black}$ as dividing $\color{blue}D2$ circles into  groups of  $\color{green}1$:[[image 0]]How many groups are there?
There are $\color{maroon}2$ groups of $\color{green}1$.[[image 0]]
$\color{blue}\color{black}2\color{black} \div \color{green}1\color{black} = \color{maroon}2\color{black}$
